<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lap2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lap,</orth> vb. to wrap up, to envelop: <cit><quote>all thy friends are --ed in lead,</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 396" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 396</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he did l. me in his own garments,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.115" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 115</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed in proof,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.2.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 2, 54</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed in a most curious mantle,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.360" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 360</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>